The paper deals with verification of relational multiagent systems (RMASs) that manipulate databases, which involves concepts from logic (temporal properties expressed in first-order mu-calculus), artificial intelligence (multiagent systems), and databases. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DB (Databases), cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
